  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "cc1e8082-09b3-4721-91e9-3230e97fb2ac",
    "name": "Waste Management",
    "description": "# Waste Management API\n\nA lightweight set of administrative and operations endpoints for managing waste sections, smoking zones, locations, and user/admin access in the Community App. This collection is intended for backend/admin workflows such as authentication, CRUD operations on waste sections and smoking zones, and fetching locations and user details.\n\n## Authentication\n\nMost requests are unauthenticated or use simple form bodies; however, if your API requires auth, set it using a Bearer token:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {{token}}\n\n ```\n\n- Base URL variable: `{{wasteurl}}`\n    \n- Some requests in this collection already use absolute URLs ([https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/](https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/)...). Others reference `{{wasteurl}}`. Keep your environment configured so both patterns work. If you consolidate later, prefer `{{wasteurl}}` for consistency.\n    \n\nIf your API issues a token after login, save it to your environment as `token` and inherit at the collection or request level.\n\n## Environments\n\nActive environment: PROD.\n\nRelevant variables to configure:\n\n- `wasteurl` – Base URL for the waste services, for example: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api`\n    \n- `email` – Generic account email if used by your endpoints.\n    \n- `emailwastr` – Waste admin/user email if used by auth endpoints.\n    \n\nNote: Only populate non-secret values in plain environment variables. Place secrets in the Postman Vault or use environment secret masking.\n\n## Quickstart (Suggested Workflow)\n\n1) Admin Authentication\n\n- wasteadminregister (POST {{wasteurl}}/wasteadminregister)\n    \n- wasteadminlogin (POST {{wasteurl}}/wasteadminlogin)\n    \n- If a token is returned, save it to `{{token}}` and set collection-level Bearer token.  \n    2) Manage Waste Sections\n    \n- addwastesection → getwastesection → updatewastesection → deletewastesection  \n    3) Manage Smoking Zones\n    \n- addsmokingzone → getsmokingzone → updatesmokingzone → deletesmokingzone  \n    4) Locations and User Details\n    \n- getlocations\n    \n- getuserdetails\n    \n\nRun requests top-to-bottom within each group to follow a typical CRUD lifecycle.\n\n## Request Summaries\n\nBelow are concise summaries; replace with your actual payload keys.\n\n1. wasteadminregister\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `{{wasteurl}}/wasteadminregister`\n        \n    - Purpose: Register a waste admin account.\n        \n    - Body: { \"email\": \"{{emailwastr}}\", \"password\": \"\", \"name\": \"\", ... }\n        \n2. wasteadminlogin\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `{{wasteurl}}/wasteadminlogin`\n        \n    - Purpose: Authenticate as waste admin and receive a token.\n        \n    - Body: { \"email\": \"{{emailwastr}}\", \"password\": \"\" }\n        \n3. addsmokingzone\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/addsmokingzone`\n        \n    - Purpose: Create a new smoking zone.\n        \n    - Body: { \"name\": \"\", \"locationId\": \"\", ... }\n        \n4. addwastesection\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/addwastesection`\n        \n    - Purpose: Create a new waste section.\n        \n    - Body: { \"name\": \"\", \"locationId\": \"\", ... }\n        \n5. updatesmokingzone\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/updatesmokingzone`\n        \n    - Purpose: Update an existing smoking zone.\n        \n    - Body: { \"zoneId\": \"\", \"name\": \"\", ... }\n        \n6. updatewastesection\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/updatewastesection`\n        \n    - Purpose: Update an existing waste section.\n        \n    - Body: { \"sectionId\": \"\", \"name\": \"\", ... }\n        \n7. deletesmokingzone\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/deletesmokingzone`\n        \n    - Purpose: Delete a smoking zone.\n        \n    - Body: { \"zoneId\": \"\" }\n        \n8. deletewastesection\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/deletewastesection`\n        \n    - Purpose: Delete a waste section.\n        \n    - Body: { \"sectionId\": \"\" }\n        \n9. getwastesection\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/getwastesection`\n        \n    - Purpose: Retrieve waste sections list/details.\n        \n    - Body: { \"filter\": \"\" }\n        \n10. getsmokingzone\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/getsmokingzone`\n        \n    - Purpose: Retrieve smoking zones list/details.\n        \n    - Body: { \"filter\": \"\" }\n        \n11. getlocations\n    \n    - Method: POST\n        \n    - Path: `https://jewapropertypro.com/infinity/jewaapp/api/getlocations`\n        \n    - Purpose: Retrieve list of locations available for sections/zones.\n        \n    - Body: { \"filter\": \"\" }\n        \n12. getuserdetails\n    \n    - Method: GET\n        \n    - Path:\n        \n    - Purpose: Retrieve current or specified user details.\n        \n    - Params: { \"userId\": \"\" }\n        \n\nNote: Some endpoints use absolute URLs, others use `{{wasteurl}}`. Ensure your environment has `wasteurl` set if you switch requests to use the variable.\n\n## Testing and Monitoring\n\nCollection-level post-response tests currently assert:\n\n- Status code is 200\n    \n- Response time is under 3000 ms\n    \n\nThese tests apply to every request. If your API returns non-200 for expected flows (e.g., 201 for create, 204 for delete, or 4xx/5xx for negative tests), consider moving or overriding tests at the request/folder level to avoid false failures.\n\nTo monitor uptime and regressions, create a monitor on this collection, schedule it (e.g., every 5–15 minutes), and add notifications to email/Slack. Use environments per deployment (PROD/SIT/Staging) to compare results across environments.\n\n## Run in Postman\n\nAdd this button to quickly import and run the collection (auto-updates when you share the latest):\n\n<a href=\"https://god.gw.postman.com/run-collection/13408795-cc1e8082-09b3-4721-91e9-3230e97fb2ac\"><img src=\"https://run.pstmn.io/button.svg\" alt=\"Run in Postman\"></a>\n\n  \n  \n\n## Versioning and Support\n\n- Versioning: Update this description when you introduce breaking changes. Consider adding a version variable (e.g., `{{api_version}}`) to the base path if the backend exposes versioned routes.\n    \n- Changelog: Use the collection changelog to track edits to requests and tests.\n    \n- Support: Document contact details for your team or link to your internal support channel. For public docs, you can publish documentation and optionally attach environments to illustrate variable usage.",
