        "description": "Summary  \nRegisters a new waste management admin user.\n\nEndpoint and Method\n\n- POST {{waste_url}}/wasteadminregister\n    \n\nAuthentication\n\n- Typically requires no prior auth for initial registration unless specified by the API. If your deployment requires auth, use the appropriate scheme configured at the collection/folder level.\n    \n\nRequest Body\n\n- Content-Type: application/json\n    \n- Schema (fields are required unless noted):\n    - fname: string – Admin’s first name\n        \n    - lname: string – Admin’s last name\n        \n    - phone: string – Admin’s contact phone\n        \n    - email: string – Email address for the new admin (must be unique). This request uses a generated value from the environment variable {{email2111}}.\n        \n    - password: string – Plaintext password provided via a secure variable {{vault:password}}\n        \n\nExample Request Body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"fname\": \"fname\",\n  \"lname\": \"lname\",\n  \"phone\": \"phone\",\n  \"email\": \"{{email2111}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{vault:password}}\"\n}\n\n ```\n\nVariables Used\n\n- {{waste_url}}: Base URL for the Waste Management service (from the active environment; currently PROD).\n    \n- {{email2111}}: Randomized email set in the request pre-request script for uniqueness per run.\n    \n- {{vault:password}}: Secure password sourced from the Postman Vault.\n    \n\nExpected Responses\n\n- 200 OK – Registration successful. Response body includes a userdetails array; tests validate status, timing, and that response email matches {{email2111}}.\n    \n- 4xx – Validation or client errors (e.g., missing/invalid fields, duplicate email). Response body typically describes the error.\n    \n- 5xx – Server error.\n    \n\nSaved Examples\n\n- [Positive - wasteadminregister](https://example/13408795-9801bd8b-3545-411e-be4b-71463e1...)\n    \n- [When registration is success](https://example/13408795-9d146ed7-da7b-4014-a9d4-23e1f92...)\n    \n\nNotes\n\n- Ensure the PROD environment has waste_url configured. The pre-request script sets {{email2111}} automatically before send. Password is pulled from the Vault; do not hardcode secrets in environments or bodies."
      },
